trFanart1":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/fanart/upsrru1424614023.jpg","strFanart2":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/fanart/tpqrqw1424614117.jpg","strFanart3":null,"strFanart4":null,"strCreativeCommons":"No","strLocked":"unlocked","strLastName":"Cristante"},{"idPlayer":"34258387","idTeam":"133682","idTeam2":null,"idTeamNational":null,"idAPIfootball":"446067","idPlayerManager":null,"idWikidata":null,"idTransferMkt":"962125","idESPN":"371608","strNationality":"Spain","strPlayer":"Buba Sangaré","strPlayerAlternate":"Aboubacar Sangaré Traoré","strTeam":"Roma","strTeam2":"","strSport":"Soccer","intSoccerXMLTeamID":null,"dateBorn":"2007-08-06","dateDied":null,"strNumber":"66","dateSigned":null,"strSigning":"","strWage":"","strOutfitter":"","strKit":"","strAgent":"","strBirthLocation":"Elche, Spain","strEthnicity":"Black","strStatus":"Active","strDescriptionEN":"Aboubacar \"Buba\" Sangaré Traoré (born 6 August 2007) is a Spanish professional footballer who plays as a right-back for Serie A club Roma.\r\n\r\nClub career\r\nBorn in Elche to Malian parents, Sangaré joined Levante's youth setup in September 2018, from Ilicitano Sporting CF. After progressing through the youth setup and alternating between the squads of Levante and affiliated club Patacona, he started to train with the first team under manager Javier Calleja in November 2023.\r\n\r\nOn 6 December 2023, before even having appeared for the reserves, Sangaré made his professional debut by starting in a 1–0 home loss to Amorebieta, for the season's Copa del Rey; aged 16 years and four months, he became the youngest player to play his first match for the club. He went on to make two more appearances for Levante's first team in the league.\r\n\r\nOn 1 July 2024, Sangaré joined Italian side Roma for an undisclosed fee, reported to be in the region of €1.5–2 million.\r\n\r\nInternational career\r\nSangaré represented Spain at under-15, under-16 and under-17 levels.","strDescriptionDE":nu